I've lived in the valley for 8 years and this was my first time at a Whole Foods Market (sad, I know)!
This location recently opened which happens to be very close to my work.
I went with a co-worker for lunch and was able to eat on the outdoor patio.
The hot and cold bars had anything you could imagine.
On Wednesday's the also offer $2 off per lb.
I ate from the hot bar and my co-worker ate from the salad bar, we were both admiring each others food the whole time!
We walked around the store after lunch, it was set up very nice and we both enjoyed looking at the different/unusual products they had to offer.
I will definitely be back for lunch again!

This is the best Whole Foods I have ever been to.
I go here just about everyday when I am staying in this area in Phoenix.
Everyone is SO nice here, it is like Mister Roger's neighborhood!
At the juice bar, if you want to request your own juice, they will actually go into the produce section and grab the vegetable you requested to juice!
The produce is clean, of course, and always in stock.
They have the best salad bar here!
I wish they always had the fresh pressed young coconut water in their pre-made fresh pressed juice section, but it is okay, when I go and it is in stock, I make sure to stock up on as much coconut water as I can for the next 2-3 days!

